The paper deals with a problem of multiple users sharing channels in a communication network, which is a typical problem in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes an algorithm for learning a stable configuration, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The experiments conducted in the paper involve comparison to state-of-the-art algorithms, which is a common practice in machine learning (cs.LG).
